# CharacterData Interface

## Goal
Implement CharacterData abstract interface that serves as the base for Text, Comment, and ProcessingInstruction nodes.

## Context
- **File**: `webidl/src/dom/character_data.zig` (create new)
- **Extends**: Node (100% complete)
- **Spec**: WHATWG DOM Standard §4.7 - CharacterData
- **IDL**: `specs/dom.md` lines ~3100-3150

## What to Implement

### 1. Core Field
```zig
pub const CharacterData = webidl.interface(struct {
    pub const extends = Node;

    /// The character data (text content)
    data: []const u8,
});
```

### 2. Attribute Getters/Setters (2)
```zig
/// data getter - IDL: [CEReactions] attribute DOMString data;
pub fn get_data(self: *const CharacterData) webidl.DOMString

/// data setter
pub fn set_data(self: *CharacterData, value: webidl.DOMString) !void

/// length getter - IDL: readonly attribute unsigned long length;
pub fn get_length(self: *const CharacterData) webidl.UnsignedLong
```

### 3. Text Manipulation Methods (5)
Per spec §4.7, implement these methods:

```zig
/// substringData(offset, count)
/// Extract substring from data
pub fn call_substringData(self: *const CharacterData, offset: u32, count: u32) !webidl.DOMString

/// appendData(data)  
/// Append to existing data
pub fn call_appendData(self: *CharacterData, data_arg: webidl.DOMString) !void

/// insertData(offset, data)
/// Insert data at offset
pub fn call_insertData(self: *CharacterData, offset: u32, data_arg: webidl.DOMString) !void

/// deleteData(offset, count)
/// Delete count characters starting at offset
pub fn call_deleteData(self: *CharacterData, offset: u32, count: u32) !void

/// replaceData(offset, count, data)
/// Replace count characters at offset with data
pub fn call_replaceData(self: *CharacterData, offset: u32, count: u32, data_arg: webidl.DOMString) !void
```

### 4. Error Handling
Throw IndexSizeError when:
- offset > length
- offset + count > length (for some operations)

### 5. Build System
Add to `build.zig`:
```zig
const character_data_mod = b.createModule(.{
    .root_source_file = b.path("webidl/generated/dom/character_data.zig"),
    .target = target,
    .imports = \u0026.{
        .{ .name = "infra", .module = infra_mod },
        .{ .name = "webidl", .module = webidl_mod },
        .{ .name = "node", .module = node_mod },
        .{ .name = "event_target", .module = event_target_mod },
    },
});
dom_mod.addImport("character_data", character_data_mod);
```

### 6. Comprehensive Tests (15+)
```zig
test "CharacterData - get/set data" { ... }
test "CharacterData - length returns correct value" { ... }
test "CharacterData - substringData extracts substring" { ... }
test "CharacterData - substringData with bounds" { ... }
test "CharacterData - appendData appends to end" { ... }
test "CharacterData - insertData at position" { ... }
test "CharacterData - insertData at start" { ... }
test "CharacterData - insertData at end" { ... }
test "CharacterData - deleteData removes characters" { ... }
test "CharacterData - deleteData handles bounds" { ... }
test "CharacterData - replaceData replaces substring" { ... }
test "CharacterData - error on offset > length" { ... }
// ... more edge case tests
```

## IDL Reference
```webidl
interface CharacterData : Node {
  [CEReactions] attribute DOMString data;
  readonly attribute unsigned long length;
  DOMString substringData(unsigned long offset, unsigned long count);
  [CEReactions] undefined appendData(DOMString data);
  [CEReactions] undefined insertData(unsigned long offset, DOMString data);
  [CEReactions] undefined deleteData(unsigned long offset, unsigned long count);
  [CEReactions] undefined replaceData(unsigned long offset, unsigned long count, DOMString data);
};
```

## Success Criteria
- ✅ File created with CharacterData interface
- ✅ All 2 attributes (data, length) implemented
- ✅ All 5 methods implemented with spec-compliant algorithms
- ✅ Error handling for out-of-bounds access
- ✅ 15+ tests covering all methods and edge cases
- ✅ No memory leaks
- ✅ Build system integrated
- ✅ All tests pass

## Reference Files
- `webidl/src/dom/node.zig` - Inheritance pattern
- `specs/dom.md` - §4.7 CharacterData spec

## Time Estimate
~2-3 hours (5 methods with string manipulation + tests)

## Enables
- whatwg-dl2 (Text node) - depends on this
- whatwg-j1x (Comment node) - depends on this

## Can Be Done In Parallel With
- whatwg-3kk, whatwg-zio (Element work)

# Element Interface - Foundation

## Goal
Create the foundational Element interface file that extends Node. This is the first step in implementing the most important DOM node type.

## Context
- **File**: `webidl/src/dom/element.zig`
- **Extends**: Node (100% complete in `node.zig`)
- **Spec**: WHATWG DOM Standard §4.8 - https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#interface-element
- **IDL Reference**: `specs/dom.md` lines ~3200-3300

## What to Implement

### 1. File Structure
```zig
const std = @import("std");
const webidl = @import("webidl");
const infra = @import("infra");
const Node = @import("node").Node;

pub const Element = webidl.interface(struct {
    pub const extends = Node;

    // Fields will be added in next issue (whatwg-zio)

    pub fn init(allocator: std.mem.Allocator, tag_name: []const u8) !Element {
        // Basic initialization
    }

    pub fn deinit(self: *Element) void {
        // Cleanup
    }
});
```

### 2. Basic Setup
- Import required modules (Node, webidl, infra)
- Create Element struct extending Node
- Add placeholder for tag name (will be implemented in next issue)
- Add basic init/deinit (minimal, will be expanded)

### 3. Build System Integration
Add to `build.zig`:
```zig
const element_mod = b.createModule(.{
    .root_source_file = b.path("webidl/generated/dom/element.zig"),
    .target = target,
    .imports = &.{
        .{ .name = "infra", .module = infra_mod },
        .{ .name = "webidl", .module = webidl_mod },
        .{ .name = "node", .module = node_mod },
        .{ .name = "event_target", .module = event_target_mod },
    },
});
dom_mod.addImport("element", element_mod);
```

### 4. Basic Test
```zig
test "Element - can create instance" {
    const allocator = std.testing.allocator;

    var element = try Element.init(allocator, "div");
    defer element.deinit();

    // Basic validation
    try std.testing.expect(element.get_nodeType() == Node.ELEMENT_NODE);
}
```

## Success Criteria
- ✅ File `webidl/src/dom/element.zig` created
- ✅ Element extends Node properly
- ✅ `zig build codegen` runs successfully
- ✅ `zig build` compiles without errors
- ✅ Basic test passes
- ✅ Ready for core implementation (whatwg-zio)

## Reference Implementation
- Study `webidl/src/dom/node.zig` for patterns
- Look at how Node extends EventTarget
- Follow same structure and style

## Time Estimate
~30 minutes (mostly setup and build system)

## Next Steps
After completion, move to whatwg-zio (Element Core) to implement actual functionality.

# Element - Attribute Manipulation Methods

## Goal
Implement full attribute manipulation API for Element nodes.

## Prerequisites
- ✅ whatwg-zio (Element Core) must be complete
- ⚠️ whatwg-74l (Attr interface) should be complete but can work without

## Context
- **File**: `webidl/src/dom/element.zig` (already exists)
- **Spec**: WHATWG DOM §4.8 - Element attribute methods
- **Critical**: Enables full element manipulation

## What to Implement

### 1. Attributes Storage Field
Add to Element struct:
```zig
/// Attributes list (ordered)
attributes: infra.List(struct { name: []const u8, value: []const u8 }),
```

Or use Attr if whatwg-74l is done:
```zig
attributes: infra.List(*Attr),
```

### 2. Attribute Query Methods (4)
```zig
/// hasAttribute(name) - IDL: boolean hasAttribute(DOMString qualifiedName);
pub fn call_hasAttribute(self: *const Element, name: webidl.DOMString) webidl.boolean

/// hasAttributeNS(ns, local) - IDL: boolean hasAttributeNS(DOMString? namespace, DOMString localName);
pub fn call_hasAttributeNS(self: *const Element, namespace: ?webidl.DOMString, local_name: webidl.DOMString) webidl.boolean

/// getAttribute(name) - IDL: DOMString? getAttribute(DOMString qualifiedName);
pub fn call_getAttribute(self: *const Element, name: webidl.DOMString) ?webidl.DOMString

/// getAttributeNS(ns, local) - IDL: DOMString? getAttributeNS(DOMString? namespace, DOMString localName);
pub fn call_getAttributeNS(self: *const Element, namespace: ?webidl.DOMString, local_name: webidl.DOMString) ?webidl.DOMString
```

### 3. Attribute Manipulation Methods (4)
```zig
/// setAttribute(name, value) - IDL: [CEReactions] undefined setAttribute(DOMString qualifiedName, DOMString value);
pub fn call_setAttribute(self: *Element, name: webidl.DOMString, value: webidl.DOMString) !void

/// setAttributeNS(ns, qualified, value) - IDL: [CEReactions] undefined setAttributeNS(DOMString? namespace, DOMString qualifiedName, DOMString value);
pub fn call_setAttributeNS(self: *Element, namespace: ?webidl.DOMString, qualified_name: webidl.DOMString, value: webidl.DOMString) !void

/// removeAttribute(name) - IDL: [CEReactions] undefined removeAttribute(DOMString qualifiedName);
pub fn call_removeAttribute(self: *Element, name: webidl.DOMString) void

/// removeAttributeNS(ns, local) - IDL: [CEReactions] undefined removeAttributeNS(DOMString? namespace, DOMString localName);
pub fn call_removeAttributeNS(self: *Element, namespace: ?webidl.DOMString, local_name: webidl.DOMString) void
```

### 4. Advanced Methods (3) - Can defer
```zig
/// toggleAttribute(name) - IDL: [CEReactions] boolean toggleAttribute(DOMString qualifiedName, optional boolean force);
pub fn call_toggleAttribute(self: *Element, name: webidl.DOMString, force: ?webidl.boolean) !webidl.boolean

/// getAttributeNames() - IDL: sequence<DOMString> getAttributeNames();
pub fn call_getAttributeNames(self: *const Element) ![]const webidl.DOMString

// getAttributeNode, setAttributeNode if Attr is done
```

### 5. Integration
- Update Element.id getter/setter to use attributes
- Update Element.className getter/setter to use attributes
- Ensure namespace attributes work with Node namespace methods

### 6. Tests (20+)
```zig
test "Element - setAttribute creates attribute" { ... }
test "Element - setAttribute updates existing" { ... }
test "Element - getAttribute returns value" { ... }
test "Element - getAttribute returns null when missing" { ... }
test "Element - hasAttribute checks existence" { ... }
test "Element - removeAttribute removes attribute" { ... }
test "Element - removeAttribute on non-existent is noop" { ... }
test "Element - setAttributeNS with namespace" { ... }
test "Element - getAttributeNS with namespace" { ... }
test "Element - multiple attributes" { ... }
test "Element - attribute name case sensitivity" { ... }
test "Element - toggleAttribute toggles" { ... }
