# Text Node Implementation

## Goal
Implement Text node - the most fundamental content node in the DOM.

## Prerequisites
- ✅ whatwg-1o1 (CharacterData) must be complete first
- ✅ Node interface complete (it is)

## Context
- **File**: `webidl/src/dom/text.zig` (create new)
- **Extends**: CharacterData
- **Spec**: WHATWG DOM §4.7 - Text interface
- **Used By**: All text content in DOM trees

## What to Implement

### 1. Text Interface
```zig
const CharacterData = @import("character_data").CharacterData;

pub const Text = webidl.interface(struct {
    pub const extends = CharacterData;

    /// wholeText cached value (optional optimization)
    whole_text_cache: ?[]const u8,
});
```

### 2. Constructor
```zig
pub fn init(allocator: std.mem.Allocator, data: []const u8) !Text {
    // Initialize CharacterData parent
    // Set node_type to TEXT_NODE (3)
    // Set node_name to "#text"
    // Set data field
}
```

### 3. Readonly Attribute (1)
```zig
/// wholeText getter - IDL: readonly attribute DOMString wholeText;
/// Spec: Returns concatenation of data of contiguous Text nodes
pub fn get_wholeText(self: *const Text) !webidl.DOMString
```

### 4. Methods (1)
```zig
/// splitText(offset) - IDL: [CEReactions, NewObject] Text splitText(unsigned long offset);
/// Spec: Splits text node at offset, returns new Text node with second half
pub fn call_splitText(self: *Text, offset: u32) !*Text
```

### 5. Integration with Node
Text nodes should:
- Work with Node.textContent (already implemented)
- Work with Node.normalize() (already implemented - merges adjacent Text nodes)
- Have nodeValue return the data

